RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 36300. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAMURAI CHALLENGE settled in mid-pack on the rail, began to pick up horses starting to rally in midturn, shifted outside gaining momentum at the quarter pole and closed strongly outside foes in the five path to get up right at the wire for the well timed late surge. BE ON NOTICE was nestled on the fence behind the engaging duo along the backside, patiently waited inside throughout the turn, pounced shifted outside in the three path at the top of the lane, took command at the sixteenth pole and just missed holding for the win in a tight photo at the wire. QUANDALE watched the front pair contesting for the lead three wide on the outside, kept pace with the leaders through the turn, angled outside in the four path straightening for home and determinedly finished up to be a clear third at the finish. ISSANO stalked near the rear in the beginning, began to lengthen stride three furlongs from the wire, rallied in the two path turning for home, burst between the tiring early leaders at the furlong pole and got up for a minor role in the end. COMPUTER HACKER had a slim lead pressured outside down the back straight, continued up front having a narrow advantage inside throughout the turn, was clinging to the lead inside at the furlong marker but faded in the final sixteenth. SCAT FACTOR travelled in midfield on the outside down the backside, made no progress running outside in the third flight around the bend and could not get involved down the stretch. WETIKO pressed the pace outside in the beginning, hounded the frontrunner around the bend, dueled for the lead with rivals on each side turning for home, could not find more late and retreated at the furlong marker. UNDER BUDGET co-trailed on the outside down the backstretch, was roused on the turn making little impression and showed some interest to the wire closing the gap on rivals at the finish. HURRICANE DESHAMBO was away slowly on the break, co-trailed on the inside down the back straight, could not keep up through the turn and was a non factor in the stretch.

DREAMS AND SCHEMES travelled three deep outside foes in midfield at the half mile marker, was hard ridden four wide on the outside midway on the turn, was fanned out widest in the seven path turning for home and passed tired rivals down the stretch. ROCKET RILEY could see the field outside runners at the half, offered a mild run two wide between horses with five sixteenths remaining and had nothing to give in the stretch drive. FOREST VIXEN settled in mid-pack with runners on each side tracking the front duo down the back straight, was urged three wide between horses in midturn, maintained position through to the top of the lane and yielded in the six path between foes at the sixteenth pole. AWMIK SIDE OF TOWN was slow into stride at the break having one other poor starter beaten down the backside, could not keep up with others three furlongs out and lost contact with the field around the turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 11 6F All Weather Track CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 27700. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VENTI settled patiently under a good hold rating kindly down the backside, pulled the rider to the lead three wide circling horses around the turn, took control turning for home and cruised to the finish for the victory. SMOKIN HOLIDAY tracked three deep at the half, was hard ridden but could no go on with the winner circling horses at the five sixteenth marker, chased in vain through the stretch under a vigorous ride and just held at the wire for place. STREET SERENADE broke inwards brushing the gate at the start, trailed down the backside, uncorked his run on the fence in midturn, split foes closing in down the lane at the eighth pole and finished up well to be a clear third in the end. IT'S ME MARIO tracked the pacesetter on the rail, kept pace through the turn, angled outside in the four path straightening out for the drive and finished up mildly to the wire to hold on battling for the minors. HARPER CITY tracked on the rail early on, was shuffled in tight quarters on the fence entering the turn and showed some late interest in the stretch to battle for the minors at the wire. BROTHER BELEN broke sharp to ne near the lead early on, was throttled back on the fence to travel in mid-pack at the half, midway on the bend was asked for run but made little headway through the turn and could not get involved through the stretch on the wrong lead to the finish line. OPEECHEE had one beat down the backside, was roused to go after the leaders three wide at the quarter pole, offered little response and passed a straggler down the stretch. SING DIXIE emerged from the pack with the lead running in hand at the half, continued up front around the bend, was collared outside by runners at the quarter pole and backed away through the field on the fence down the stretch.
